      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HELLO PECK (1) was strongly fancied last time on the back of some superb recent form, including a four-run winning streak, but could only manage second (29.83) at this track. Deserves serious consideration. RAINBOW SHOUT (5) was safely held last time out, finishing eighth at Richmond over 520m behind Show More (30.86) in a Mix. Safe beginner but has a tricky box to overcome. Worth another chance. BAD KNEES (8) showed good pace from out wide and was prominent early but began to paddle and faded out of it when 6th at this track in Grade 5 company. The form from his last run stacks up well. Shapes as one to consider. PITMAN RINGO (2) was unplaced here last start but gets his chance to atone.",
